to\nfollow.\u201d\u201d They won't onn their\neyes and look where the sun is\nshining on fields waving with\nripe to the harvest and m\u2018\nGod's abundant bounty everywhere\nvisible. They simply cling to the\nnotion that things are going wfong\nand refuse to be comforted. Our\ncontemporary, the New York\u2018\nTimes, in a recent issue collated\nand presented an array of -mx;c-\u2018\nconcerning the business outlook\nwhich should reassnre all who bave\nindulged the apprehension that the\u2018\ncourse of legislation in Congress\nmight bave drawn its lnfornzion\u2018\nfrom the best trade sources through\not the country, and all report bus\niness good and steadily growing\nbetter. The textile trade outlook\nis excellent; the wcolen trade is\nreducing prices but not wages; the\nlinen trade prospects are very good.\nCrops, according to an examination\njust concluded by a leading bank\nthe Continental and Commercial\u2014\nare phenomenal, wheat showing\n9,000,000 bushels more than last\nyear, 170,000,000 over the domestic\nneed. Corn, even though it suffered\nthrough drought, will be more than\nan average crop, and there isa big\nreserve from last year besides. The\nhay crop will be worth $1.000.000,-\n000. Then our foreign trade is\nalready $421.000,000 in excess of\n1912, and of exports alone the\nfarmers will receive over $180,000.-\n000, nearly double the amount of a\nyear ago. These are only a few of\nthe figures; but they show the\ngeneral unmistakable evidences of\nsubstantial business prosperity all\nalong the line. The year promises\nto be a record one in all branches\nof business. We commend the\nshowing to the doubting ones. Let\nthem look up and take courage.\u2014\nChristain Herald.\nGrowth of the Pettery Industry.\nThe manufacture of pottery is one of\nthe mnet imporiant branches of the\nclay-working industry in the Usited\n!m During the year 1912 pottery\n\u2018was produced to the valoe of 53\u00a2,504,164\nsccording to the annual chart just\nissued by the United States Geological\nSurvey, showing tbe production of all\nclay products. compiled by Jefferson\nMiddieton. This figure indicates a\nhealthy coudition of the pottery indue\ntry, the increased value of the output\nfor 1912 over 1911 being almast $2,000,-\n000. Ohio was by far the largest pro\nducer in 1912, bwing credited with\n$15,508,735, New Jersey was next, with\nover $5,000.000. Bix states produced\npottery to the value of $1,000,000.\nBeware of Ointments for\nCatarrh That Contain Mercury\nmercury will ly dest he\nsmell and m\ufb02y '::u\u2018 \u201c\ufb02\nwhole system when entering \u201cnm\n\u2018-h:v: be u'-\u2018d ex: M:' n\u2018:e.\ufb02.uou\nfiom n\u2018mubu phy-?c\ufb01u. u\u2019tho damage\nthey will do is ten fold to the gnod you\ncan possibly derive from them. l,!lnll\u2018l\ng\u2018mh Cure, m-uh\ufb02snd by F. J\nCo., Toledo, D.,, contains no\nmercury, and k.ulu internally, acting\n:mtly u?\ufb02l the blood and mm%mr\u2018\nof the system. In buying Hall's\n(\u2018lur;h Cure be sure you get the genu\nIt in taken internally and\nKoiedo. Ohto, by F. J. Cheney\ntimonials free.\nSold by Drugsists, Price To per bottle.\nTake Hall's Family Pills for ecastipation.\nNEW FURNITURE STORE\nA full line of mnew and second hand\nFurniture, Stoves, Beds, Etc. 4\nCall and inspect this stock.\nI also have one office room and four other rooms for rent on the\nsecond floor of the Bopp building. 3\nH. L. MORGAN, Proprietor\nDOLORES, COLORADO\nG s ss B\n\u201cWmm\u201cmm\nCOLORADO-NEW MEXICO FAIR\nSeptember 23, 24, 26 and 26, 1913\nAEROPLANE FLIGHTS DAILY\n8 Bands, Street Carnival, De Kreno\u2019s 7 Oriental Street Shows\nFREE STREET ATTRACTIONS\nIndustrial and Automobile Parade, Base Ball, Indians, Eto., Eto\nCOME ALL\nua- of .a Meontezuma County\nbe in Septem\nand &o 2 3\nSecond Day, Ostober 1, 1913\n190 p. m.~Moutesuma County Motar Club\nil sl e, ok o 0;\nAl e eek AR\ney 2, R\n\nThird Day, October 2, 1913\nur-- County school children's parade.\n.F}L e 2 A\ns 1008