ty dwellings in\ni Greeley, Fort Collins, and Longmont who want to trade for\nMontezuma Valley lands. Any persons who have land that\nthey care to trade for any lands or city property in these local\nities will please give me your listment and good description, g\nand say about what you care to trade for. Those anxious to\ndispose of property must expect to do some trading as the cash\n4 transfers will be very few for some time yet.\nl DOLORES, COLORADOJ\nUV YUYV YV VYV VYV VS Y Y Y\ne\nmw\u201c\u201c-\u201c\u2018\u201c\ufb02\nVELIE AUTOMOBILES E\nThey are unsurpassed for either\ntouring or pleasure driving. Ful- E\nly equipped with Gray Davis\ni ELECTRIC LIGHTS AND ELECTRIC SELF STARTER\nLook them over before you\npurchase. We are pleased to\ndemonstrate if interested\niThe Rust Lumber Merc. Co.\nvmvmvvmwvvv\nTHE STALLION, MIKE\nSTOCK STKRL DUST,\nWill stand this season at\nplace, one mile south of Beula\nschool house and north-west from\nCortez, or, if I am notified, will\nbring him to the place where the\nmare or mares are,\nMIKR'S GOOD POINTS.\nA medium sized all round farg\nhorse, has many good colts in thig\nnllo\u2018. bas bu: a good race\ngentle, easy keeper, good\npuller and a sure footer,\nTerms, $5.00 when the mare is\nknown to be with .foal, or $8.00\nwhen the colt is 10 days old.\nCuanLEy MiLLxn, Owser,\nCortez, Colorado.","height":"21800","width":"15580"}}
